INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'a7e51bdf-0707-4da4-9814-43ec9e97693e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Vue Code Quality — eslint-plugin-vue, Naming Conventions, and the 50-Line Composable Rule$escape$,
  $escape$Vue's official linter, `eslint-plugin-vue`, enforces patterns the core team considers non-negotiable. Use the `vue3-recommended` ruleset as your baseline — it catches multi-root template misuse, v-bind shorthand drift, and unordered component options. Beyond the preset, add `vue/component-name-in-template-casing: ['error', 'PascalCase']` to ban `<my-button>` in favor of `<MyButton>`, and `vue/prop-name-casing: ['error', 'camelCase']` to keep prop declarations consistent with JavaScript conventions while templates use kebab-case automatically.

For composables, enforce the `use` prefix with `vue/custom-event-name-casing` and a local ESLint rule or team convention: every file in `composables/` must export a single function named `useX`. Keep that function under 50 lines — if `useUserProfile` grows past that, it's doing two things. Split it into `useUserData` and `useUserPermissions`. This boundary forces composables to stay single-responsibility and makes tree-shaking more predictable. Pair with `vue/define-macros-order` to standardize `defineProps` → `defineEmits` → `defineExpose` ordering in `<script setup>` blocks across your entire codebase.$escape$,
  $escape$// eslint.config.js (flat config)
import pluginVue from 'eslint-plugin-vue'

export default [
  ...pluginVue.configs['flat/recommended'],
  {
    rules: {
      'vue/component-name-in-template-casing': ['error', 'PascalCase'],
      'vue/prop-name-casing': ['error', 'camelCase'],
      'vue/define-macros-order': ['error', {
        order: ['defineProps', 'defineEmits', 'defineExpose']
      }],
      'vue/block-order': ['error', {
        order: ['script', 'template', 'style']
      }],
      'max-lines-per-function': ['warn', { max: 50 }]
    }
  }
]$escape$,
